- Seasoned sales professionals: Employees who have been with the company since before 1995;
- Salary fruit of over $50,000: Employees earning more than $50,000;
- Rating of more than 3 stars: Employees with an average performance rating greater than 3;
- Completed a significant number of training courses: Employees who have completed multiple training courses.

- "shining star" refers to the top-performing employee;
- "pinnacle of performance" refers to the highest performance rank;
- "invested in their own growth" refers to completing more than two training courses.

- "Courses taken" refers to the training courses completed or in progress by the employees;
- "Average performance ratings" are calculated from the performance reviews;
- The results are sorted first by the highest average rating, then by last name, and finally by first name.

- 'Completed' status in the `employee_training` table indicates that the training course has been finished;
- 'Rating' in the `performance_reviews` table is a measure of employee performance, typically on a scale;
- The overall average salary is calculated from all employees in the `employees` table.

- "Top-performing" refers to the highest average performance rating;
- In case of a tie in average performance ratings, the employee with the most total training hours is considered the top-performing;
- "Completed" training courses are those where the status is 'Completed'.

- "roots from the top branches to the leaves" refers to the hierarchical structure of the organization, starting from top-level managers and extending to all subordinates;
- "blooming in" refers to the department an employee belongs to;
- "nurtured" refers to the training courses completed by the employee.

- 'Gardeners' refers to employees;
- 'Seeds' refers to training courses;
- 'Full bloom' refers to the completion of training;
- 'Lengths of the seasons' refers to the duration of the training courses;
- 'Roles' refers to job titles.

- 'Blossoms' refers to employees;
- 'Nurturing greenhouses' refers to departments;
- 'Well-funded' means the department's annual budget is greater than 500,000.0;
- 'Invested in their growth' means the employee has enrolled in a training course;
- 'Spans more than 10 hours' refers to the duration of the training course.

- 'Shining stars' refers to employees who have a high performance review rating (4 or higher);
- 'Garden of Soft Skills' refers to the training courses in the 'Soft Skills' category;
- 'Completed' means the employees have finished the training course;
- 'Departments' are the units or teams within the organization to which the employees belong.

- 'Trailblazers' refers to employees who have demonstrated exceptional commitment and skill in their training;
- 'Mastered the art of technical wizardry' implies completing technical training courses;
- 'Advanced technical training course' refers to courses in the 'Technical' category with a duration of more than 40 hours;
- 'Surpassing the 40-hour mark' means the course duration is greater than 40 hours.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(employee_id) 
FROM employees 
WHERE title IN (SELECT title_name FROM titles WHERE level = 'Entry');

SELECT title_name
FROM titles
WHERE level = (SELECT MAX(level) FROM titles);
